<P>
DODGER STAR GIVES OUT COLLEGE SCHOLARSHIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pitcher Orel Hershiser handed out college scholarships to eight students at 
Dodger Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
The scholarships were awarded from a fund established in memory of James 
Patrick Jarrin, the late son of Dodger Spanish-language broadcaster Jaime 
Jarrin. James Patrick Jarrin died of an aneurysm last year at age 29. 
</P>
<P>
Hershiser is president of the fund. 
</P>
<P>
Recipients of $500 scholarships were: Mariano Aranda and Carmen Gonzalez, 
Garfield High School; Martin Hernandez and Lilia Sanchez, Lincoln High School; 
Geoffrey Heredia and Michelle Vilar, San Marino High School (which James 
Patrick Jarrin attended), and Arcelia Gomez and Martin Romero, Wilson High 
School. 
</P>
</TEXT>
