<HEADLINE>
<P>
W. T. (BILL) GRACE; FOUNDER OF CANDY SHOP CHAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
W. T. (Bill) Grace, 82, who as a shipyard worker in World War II made candy at 
night with an eye to someday owning his own store, died Saturday in a Long 
Beach hospital after undergoing heart surgery. 
</P>
<P>
Today, Helen Grace Chocolates, which he named for his first wife, consists of 
12 candy shops throughout the Los Angeles area. It also markets chocolates for 
fund-raising groups throughout the country. 
</P>
<P>
Grace is survived by his wife, Betty, two sons, six grandchildren and four 
great-grandchildren. 
</P>
</TEXT>
