<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPOTTED OWLS AND LOGGERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It is difficult to have much sympathy for a person who would display a bumper 
sticker reading "Save a Logger, Eat an Owl." The loggers assume that humans are 
unquestionably more important than a bird. There are many of us who do not 
necessarily agree that the concerns of humans give them the right to drive 
other species to extinction. The loggers will not starve to death. 
</P>
<P>
Let them find a more respectable line of work. Our country has been thoroughly 
butchered in the name of economic growth and "development" (a despicable 
euphemism). Thank God the ranks of environmentalists are growing and that now 
other species have a fighting chance. It's too late for the California grizzly 
and condor. 
</P>
<P>
LINDA BAINBRIDGE 
</P>
<P>
Altadena 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
