<HEADLINE>
<P>
SERVICE TO BE FRIDAY FOR LAW FIRM PARTNER, VICTIM OF HEART ATTACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A memorial service will be conducted Friday for a founding partner in a 
Tustin-based law firm who passed away last week after a sudden heart attack. 
</P>
<P>
The service for Scott M. McCune, 40, is to be held at 2 p.m. at Trinity 
Presbyterian Church, 17th Street and Prospect Avenue in Tustin. Donations are 
being accepted to fund a memorial scholarship at Western State University 
School of Law. Inquiries can be directed to Larry Willis at (714) 730-5700. 
</P>
<P>
McCune died Saturday at Torrance Memorial Hospital as the result of a heart 
attack, his business associates said. A specialist in insurance law, McCune in 
1975 helped found the law firm of Callahan, McCune &amp; Willis, which is based 
in Tustin and also has offices in West Los Angeles and San Diego. He also 
served as a judge pro tem in Los Angeles and Orange County courts and lectured 
to law and insurance groups. 
</P>
<P>
He is survived by his wife, Brandi; a daughter, Christina Marie, 2; a sister, 
Carol Mann of Redondo Beach, and his parents, William and Lorraine McCune of 
Huntington Harbour. 
</P>
</TEXT>
