<P>
PBS has lined up President and Mrs. Bush for their first extended TV interview 
since he took office. "The President and Mrs. Bush Talking With David Frost: A 
Unique Perspective From Kennebunkport" will be aired Sept. 5, PBS announced 
Wednesday. The program will include a review of Bush's term so far. Frost in 
the past has interviewed former Presidents Kennedy and Nixon, among other 
political leaders. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
