<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: YORBA LINDA; 
</P>
<P>
SOFTBALL TOURNEY TO AID CANCER SUPPORT GROUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Parents of children with cancer have organized a softball tournament at Yorba 
Regional Park this weekend to raise money for their support group. 
</P>
<P>
Parent-organizers Tom and Patricia McDermott and Jeff and Donna Maloney are 
hoping to raise about $6,000 this year for the UCI Cancer Center Parent Support 
Group through the tournament on Saturday and Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The cost per co-ed team is $200 and the McDermotts and Maloneys are hoping 20 
teams will play. 
</P>
<P>
For registration information, call (714) 528-3679. 
</P>
<P>
The McDermotts have a 3-year-old daughter with leukemia. The Maloneys' son, 
Jeff, died earlier this year from Burkitt's lymphoma. 
</P>
</TEXT>
