<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: AIRLINE PASSENGER TRAFFIC IN JUNE AT JOHN WAYNE GROWS 5.6% OVER 
1988; 
</P>
<P>
HOTELS/TOURISM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Mary Ann Galante, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Airline passenger traffic at John Wayne Airport increased to 415,405 in June, a 
5.6% jump compared with the 393,286 recorded during the same period last year. 
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, recently released data from John Wayne Airport shows that air 
carrier flight operations showed a 0.3% drop from levels recorded in June, 
1988, while commuter airline operations were up 74.1% for the same period. 
</P>
<P>
Total aircraft operations climbed 0.4% last month to 48,085 from 47,897 
recorded during June of last year, the airport data revealed. 
</P>
<P>
General aviation activity, which accounted for 83% of the total aircraft 
operations in June, showed a 2.7% drop when compared to the same month in 1988. 
</P>
</TEXT>
