<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Mary Ann Galante, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Carl Karcher Enterprises has signed an agreement with Cal State Fullerton to 
put a Carl's Jr. on campus. 
</P>
<P>
The restaurant, which should be built by January, is the first Carl's Jr. 
within the 20-campus California State University system. The franchisee is the 
CSUF Foundation, a university auxiliary organization. 
</P>
<P>
The Cal State Fullerton Carl's Jr. is the company's fourth restaurant on a 
college campus. The other three campuses are the University of Southern 
California, Santa Monica City College and UC Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
Karcher Enterprises operates 494 Carl's Jr. restaurants in California, Oregon, 
Arizona and Nevada. 
</P>
</TEXT>
