<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: SANTA MONICA; 
</P>
<P>
SCHOOLS SEEK COORDINATOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Santa Monica-Malibu Unified School District has established a new 
administrative position to coordinate bilingual education and other programs 
for students who speak limited English. 
</P>
<P>
The school board on Monday approved the post, with an annual salary of $43,246 
to $50,592. The coordinator will work with bilingual and English as a Second 
Language teachers and review curricula and textbooks, said Francine Geldwachs, 
director of curriculum and staff development. 
</P>
<P>
Previously, Geldwachs and a teacher on special assignment oversaw the bilingual 
and ESL programs, Geldwachs said. The coordinator position was created because 
"the programs have grown, and they're important to the district," she said. 
</P>
<P>
About 17% of the district's 9,000 students in kindergarten through 12th grade 
have limited proficiency in English, Geldwachs said. 
</P>
<P>
Job applications are available at the district offices, 1651 16th St. or by 
calling (213) 450-8338, Ext. 274. They are due Aug. 14. 
</P>
</TEXT>
