<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: CULVER CITY; 
</P>
<P>
16 PARKING PERMITS GRANTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A limited number of parking permits will be granted to residents of Higuera 
Street in Culver City who must leave their cars on cross streets when parking 
on their street is prohibited. 
</P>
<P>
The City Council on Monday voted unanimously to grant a maximum of 16 permits 
to residents of Higuera Street who live from Lucerne Avenue to southeast of 
Schaefer Street. 
</P>
<P>
Several residents have requested permits to park on cross streets, which have 
one- and two-hour limits for those without permits, according to a staff 
report. Parking on Higuera Street is prohibited during the morning and 
afternoon rush hours. 
</P>
