WESTSIDE DIGEST: CULVER CITY; 
</P>
<P>
BUYING OF POLICE CARS OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Culver City Council on Monday approved $146,000 to purchase nine Chevrolet 
Caprice sedans for the Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
The council waived its usual competitive bidding procedure to become part of a 
large-volume purchase by the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department, which has 
awarded its bid to Maurice J. Sopp &amp; Sons of Huntington Park. 
</P>
<P>
The Police Department, which uses Chevrolet Impala and Caprice patrol cars, 
plans to use six of the new cars for patrol and three for administrative 
duties, according to a staff report. 
</P>
