<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPECIAL CLASSES FOR FOREIGN STUDENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
West Los Angeles College in Culver City will offer classes and tutoring to 
foreign students in the coming academic year. 
</P>
<P>
English, business, music appreciation, travel and other courses will have 
special sections that will address issues that a foreign-born person might not 
automatically understand, said foreign student adviser Jewel D'Aloia. 
</P>
<P>
D'Aloia will teach a one-unit "Introduction to College" class that will cover 
study skills and American higher education. It will also offer information on 
health insurance, what to do after a car accident and other pointers on 
adapting to the United States, she said. 
</P>
<P>
The English department will provide sessions on reducing accents, D'Aloia said. 
</P>
<P>
Last year, about 200 of the two-year college's 9,000 students held 
foreign-student visas from 36 countries, D'Aloia said. 
</P>
<P>
For more information call (213) 836-7110, Ext. 312. 
</P>
</TEXT>
