<P>
District of Columbia Police Chief Maurice T. Turner, reported to be considering 
a race for mayor, was welcomed into the GOP today by President Bush, who called 
his switch from Democratic ranks "a major step for our party." 
</P>
<P>
Bush and the police chief, who is black, posed for pictures in the Oval Office. 
With Republican National Committee Chairman Lee Atwater seated nearby, Bush 
said: "It's a major step for our party as we try to broaden it out, and have 
the broadest possible appeal, so welcome." 
</P>
