<P>
QUEEN ENTERS HORSE IN U.S. RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHICAGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Queen Elizabeth II of England will enter a horse in the United States for the 
first time in 35 years at Arlington Park, track officials say. 
</P>
<P>
Unknown Quantity will represent her in the $200,000 Arlington Handicap on Aug. 
12. 
</P>
<P>
"I am extremely pleased Her Majesty will have a horse entered in the Arlington 
Handicap," Arlington Chairman Richard Duchossois said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
No jockey has been named for the queen's horse. 
</P>
<P>
Her last entrant in the United States was Landau, which finished last in the 
Washington, D.C., International in 1954. 
</P>
</TEXT>
